13:53.319 --> 13:55.889
HMM.

13:55.889 --> 13:58.525
FINALLY STANDING UP
TO ME, HUH?

14:01.034 --> 14:02.836
WHAT IS IT, JEFFERY?

14:07.874 --> 14:09.810
TELL YOUR FATHER.
TALK TO HIM.

14:09.810 --> 14:10.977
SON?

14:13.479 --> 14:15.549
GO ON, SON.

14:17.217 --> 14:18.885
[ SIGHS ]

14:18.885 --> 14:20.554
LOOK,
MY DINNER IS GETTING COLD

14:20.554 --> 14:22.388
AND THE CAVIAR
IS STARTING TO BREW,

14:22.388 --> 14:25.626
SO IF YOU CAN'T ACCEPT
THAT THIS IS A HAPPY OCCASION ‐‐

14:25.626 --> 14:28.695
WE ARE CELEBRATING
OUR SON'S ENGAGEMENT.

14:28.695 --> 14:30.263
IF YOU CAN'T DO THAT,
THEN YOU'RE ARE JUST GONNA

14:30.263 --> 14:32.132
HAVE TO LEAVE, SWEETHEART.
‐OH, I'M LEAVING.

14:32.132 --> 14:34.100
BUT I'M NOT LEAVING
YOU HERE.

14:34.100 --> 14:35.569
Alice: MRS. HARRINGTON?

14:35.569 --> 14:37.838
ALICE,
WE SAID THE KITCHEN.

14:37.838 --> 14:39.940
‐THIS IS IMPORTANT.
‐WELL, WHAT IS IT DEAR?

14:39.940 --> 14:41.241
PHONE.

14:43.810 --> 14:46.146
PLEASE EXCUSE ME.

14:46.146 --> 14:48.048
‐DAD, I GOT TO STAY.
‐HELLO.

14:48.048 --> 14:50.050
‐NO, YOU'RE NOT.
‐NO, I HAVE TO STAY.

14:50.050 --> 14:51.752
I CAN'T FORCE YOU
TO COME WITH ME.

14:51.752 --> 14:53.887
OH, MY GOODNESS!

14:53.887 --> 14:55.288
KATHERYN.

14:55.288 --> 14:57.691
OH, I'M SO SORRY,
KATHERYN.

14:57.691 --> 14:59.793
OH, LISTEN,
I'M ON MY WAY OVER THERE.

14:59.793 --> 15:01.835
I'M COMING OVER
RIGHT NOW.

15:01.835 --> 15:03.436
I'LL SEE YOU SHORTLY.

15:03.436 --> 15:06.439
BYE‐BYE.

15:06.439 --> 15:10.010
OH, SO MUCH DRAMA.

15:10.010 --> 15:11.477
HMM.

15:11.477 --> 15:13.013
JEFFERY, PLEASE.

15:13.013 --> 15:14.881
HE'S GONNA WANT
TO COME WITH ME.

15:14.881 --> 15:16.550
WHY IS THAT?

15:16.550 --> 15:19.686
WELL,
IT SEEMS WYATT IS DEAD.

15:19.686 --> 15:21.788
‐WHAT?
‐WHAT?

15:21.788 --> 15:23.223
O.D.'d OR SOMETHING.

15:23.223 --> 15:24.658
OH, JIM.

15:24.658 --> 15:26.426
WHAT?

15:26.426 --> 15:28.829
SON, COME WITH ME NOW.

15:32.232 --> 15:33.800
JIM.

15:33.800 --> 15:36.937
GO SEE ABOUT YOUR JIM.

15:36.937 --> 15:39.773
IT'S OKAY SWEETHEART.
I HAVE YOU.

15:39.773 --> 15:42.475
YOUR DAD'S GOT GO GO
CHECK ON JIM.

15:42.475 --> 15:44.678
HE ALWAYS DOES.

15:49.415 --> 15:53.453
FIRST, YOUR DAD'S BITCH DIES,
AND NOW YOURS DOES.

15:56.422 --> 16:00.400
IT'S KIND OF CRAZY.

16:00.400 --> 16:03.469
HMM.

16:03.469 --> 16:08.008
BUT YOU'VE ALWAYS GOT MELISSA
AND THE BABY.

16:16.883 --> 16:19.920
♪♪♪♪

16:49.382 --> 16:52.385
YOU KNOW, BENNY ALMOST
CAME CLOSE TO GETTING GOT.

16:52.385 --> 16:54.020
I KNOW.

16:54.020 --> 16:56.089
I WOULD HAVE HATED
TO DO THAT.

16:56.089 --> 16:58.725
I KNOW.

16:58.725 --> 17:00.594
WHAT THE HELL
TOOK YOU SO LONG?

17:00.594 --> 17:03.403
WE HAD TO CALL THREE BRANCHES
TO MAKE THIS HAPPEN.

17:03.403 --> 17:04.605
THAT'S WHY I'M SO LATE.

17:04.605 --> 17:06.439
BANKS CLOSED A WHILE AGO,
CANDY.

17:06.439 --> 17:09.042
I KNOW, AND I'M SORRY.

17:09.042 --> 17:11.244
IS IT ALL HERE?

17:11.244 --> 17:13.179
YES.

17:13.179 --> 17:15.381
IT'S ALL THERE, WAR.

17:18.084 --> 17:19.920
DO I NEED TO COUNT THIS?

17:19.920 --> 17:22.088
WAR, IT'S THERE.

17:22.088 --> 17:23.724
CANDY, IF I GET HOME AND THERE'S
ONE DOLLAR MISSING ‐‐

17:23.724 --> 17:25.759
WAR, IT'S ALL THERE.

17:25.759 --> 17:28.094
IT'S THERE.

17:30.997 --> 17:34.100
I DON'T THINK I EVER HAD THIS
MUCH CASH AT ONE TIME BEFORE.

17:34.100 --> 17:35.969
YOU CAME THROUGH, GIRL.

17:35.969 --> 17:37.804
YEAH, I DID.

17:37.804 --> 17:39.372
YOU ALWAYS DO.

17:39.372 --> 17:41.675
MY DAMN CANDY CANE.

17:41.675 --> 17:43.977
THAT'S ME.

17:43.977 --> 17:46.880
YEAH, YOU PULLED IT OFF,
REAL TALK.

17:46.880 --> 17:48.214
OKAY.

17:48.214 --> 17:49.716
GOOD FOR YOU.

17:49.716 --> 17:52.686
SO, ARE WE GOOD?

17:52.686 --> 17:54.387
YEAH, BABY, WE GOOD.

17:54.387 --> 17:56.456
LOOK, I KEEP MY WORD.

17:56.456 --> 17:57.824
I'M NOT THE ONE THAT LIES.

17:57.824 --> 18:00.260
I DO
WHAT I SAY I'M GONNA DO.

18:00.260 --> 18:02.569
I KNOW.

18:02.569 --> 18:05.639
AND YOU KNOW I HATE
TO NOT DO.

18:05.639 --> 18:07.641
I KNOW, THAT'S WHY
I WANT TO THANK YOU

18:07.641 --> 18:09.510
FOR GIVING ME
A LITTLE BIT MORE TIME.

18:09.510 --> 18:11.377
YOU BOUGHT THAT TIME.

18:13.514 --> 18:17.117
LOOK, CANDY,
I AM SORRY ABOUT ALL THIS.

18:17.117 --> 18:18.819
I'M...

18:18.819 --> 18:21.287
GO AHEAD, YOU CAN SAY IT.

18:21.287 --> 18:23.389
I'M SORRY, TOO.

18:23.389 --> 18:26.026
ME TOO, REALLY.

18:27.160 --> 18:30.463
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU ABOUT THE
FOUR MILLION IN THE BEGINNING.

18:30.463 --> 18:32.198
YES, YOU SHOULD HAVE.

18:32.198 --> 18:34.434
BUT THANK YOU
FOR HAVING MY BACK.

18:34.434 --> 18:37.437
I DID HAVE YOUR BACK.

18:37.437 --> 18:38.639
I KNOW.

18:38.639 --> 18:41.107
BUT I WAS GONNA BREAK IT.

18:41.107 --> 18:44.945
I KNEW THAT, TOO.

18:44.945 --> 18:48.348
THEY DON'T CALL ME WAR
FOR NOTHING, BABY.

18:48.348 --> 18:51.084
YEP.

18:51.084 --> 18:54.988
ALL RIGHT,
WE COOL AGAIN.

18:54.988 --> 18:58.158
THAT MAKES ME ‐‐
THAT MAKES ME HAPPY.

18:59.926 --> 19:01.568
I'LL SEE YOU AROUND.

19:01.568 --> 19:04.137
AT MY HOUSE?

19:04.137 --> 19:05.606
YOU KNOW,
I MIGHT STOP BY

19:05.606 --> 19:09.309
FROM TIME TO TIME
FOR A LITTLE TUNE UP.

19:09.309 --> 19:12.412
WILL I KNOW
YOU'RE COMING?

19:12.412 --> 19:14.815
LOOK, WE BACK
TO THE WAY WE WERE.

19:14.815 --> 19:16.950
ALL RIGHT,
YOU BOUGHT YOUR RESPECT BACK,

19:16.950 --> 19:19.352
TWO MILLION TIMES OVER.

19:19.352 --> 19:21.087
OKAY.

19:21.087 --> 19:22.455
ALL RIGHT.

19:22.455 --> 19:26.760
BUT IF YOU COME BY,
YOU'LL CALL FIRST?

19:26.760 --> 19:30.163
I COULD DO THAT.

19:30.163 --> 19:32.198
OKAY.

19:32.198 --> 19:33.734
YOU GONNA ANSWER?

19:33.734 --> 19:35.836
SOMETIMES.

19:35.836 --> 19:37.103
I'M KIDDING.

19:37.103 --> 19:39.840
NO, YOUR ASS NOT,
BUT IT'S COOL.

19:39.840 --> 19:41.341
YOU GOOD
AT WHAT YOU DO, BABY.

19:41.341 --> 19:43.009
BEST I EVER HAD.

19:43.009 --> 19:45.178
THEN WHY AM I PAYING <i>YOU?</i>

19:45.178 --> 19:46.446
DON'T PUSH IT.

19:49.249 --> 19:51.417
BYE.

19:51.417 --> 19:52.686
BYE.

19:52.686 --> 19:55.722
♪♪♪♪

20:04.538 --> 20:06.573
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

20:21.187 --> 20:23.223
[ CRYING ]

20:45.979 --> 20:47.447
WHY ARE YOU
JUST SITTING THERE?

20:47.447 --> 20:48.849
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

20:48.849 --> 20:50.817
MRS. CRYER JUST CALLED
AND SAID THAT WYATT GOT HURT.

20:50.817 --> 20:52.953
SHE SAID
THAT WYATT WAS DEAD.

20:52.953 --> 20:55.088
YOU'RE LYING.

20:55.088 --> 20:56.222
‐JEFFERY.
‐YOU ARE.

20:56.222 --> 20:57.791
‐ABOUT?
‐ABOUT WYATT.

20:57.791 --> 20:59.960
LET'S JUST GO OVER
TO THE CRYER'S THEN.

20:59.960 --> 21:01.267
YEAH, LET'S.

21:01.267 --> 21:03.436
OKAY.

21:03.436 --> 21:05.506
[ SIGHS ]

21:05.506 --> 21:06.773
WHY ARE YOU
JUST SITTING THERE?

21:06.773 --> 21:09.309
WOULD YOU GIVE ME A SECOND?
HE'S DEAD.

21:09.309 --> 21:11.177
THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN
DO ABOUT IT NOW.

21:11.177 --> 21:13.313
‐WHY DO YOU NEED TO BE SUCH A ‐‐
‐SAY IT.

21:13.313 --> 21:15.115
SEE, NOW THAT'S
THE KIND OF LANGUAGE

21:15.115 --> 21:17.951
THAT WILL GET YOU
A SPANKING.

21:17.951 --> 21:20.220
[ SCOFFS ]

21:20.220 --> 21:21.788
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

21:21.788 --> 21:23.156
I'M GOING TO THE CRYER'S.

21:23.156 --> 21:24.725
NOT WITHOUT ME, YOU'RE NOT.

21:24.725 --> 21:26.226
I NEED TO GO AND SEE ‐‐

21:26.226 --> 21:29.563
NO, I NEED YOU TO DRIVE ME
BECAUSE I'M DRINKING.

21:29.563 --> 21:30.631
WELL, THEN COME ON.

21:30.631 --> 21:31.832
I AM NOT READY.

21:31.832 --> 21:32.833
MOM.

21:32.833 --> 21:34.868
JEFFERY, SIT DOWN!

21:37.203 --> 21:39.272
DID YOU HEAR ME?

21:39.272 --> 21:42.208
NOW COME AND SIT DOWN,
BOY.

21:54.988 --> 21:58.992
DAMN FLORAL PRINTS.

21:58.992 --> 22:03.403
LOOK AT YOU.

22:03.403 --> 22:06.640
TEARING UP.

22:06.640 --> 22:09.743
YOU'RE GRIEVING YOUR MAN.

22:09.743 --> 22:12.746
HE'S NOT MY MAN.
HE'S MY FRIEND.

22:12.746 --> 22:14.581
WELL, NOT ANYMORE.

22:17.283 --> 22:19.786
WOW.

22:19.786 --> 22:23.156
IF LOOKS COULD KILL,
I'LL BE DEAD.

22:26.292 --> 22:29.563
DO YOU WANT ME DEAD,
JEFFERY?

22:29.563 --> 22:32.666
I'M BREATHING
AND HE'S NOT.

22:32.666 --> 22:35.769
[ SIGHS ]

22:35.769 --> 22:38.839
IT'S JUST AS WELL.

22:38.839 --> 22:42.776
HE WAS NO GOOD FOR YOU.

22:42.776 --> 22:46.547
THAT BOY
WAS RUINING YOU.

22:46.547 --> 22:50.416
NOW YOU CAN BE FREE
FOR MELISSA.

22:50.416 --> 22:53.453
WHY DON'T YOU LIKE HER,
HUH?

22:53.453 --> 22:56.923
I MEAN, SHE'S PRETTY,
SHE'S GOT A GREAT BODY,

22:56.923 --> 22:59.893
EVEN THOUGH SHE JUST EATS
WAY TOO MANY CARBS.

22:59.893 --> 23:03.570
I TOOK HER TO LUNCH
THE OTHER DAY, AND SHE SAT THERE

23:03.570 --> 23:07.708
AND JUST ORDERED EVERYTHING
FRIED AND CARBS.

23:07.708 --> 23:09.576
AND I THINK
IF SHE SAW A VEGETABLE,

23:09.576 --> 23:11.277
SHE WOULDN'T EVEN
RECOGNIZE IT.

23:11.277 --> 23:14.114
SHE'S JUST, WELL...

23:14.114 --> 23:16.182
YOU KNOW,
IT'S TYPICAL OF THESE

23:16.182 --> 23:19.185
POOR BLACK GIRLS BORN
IN THE HOOD.

23:19.185 --> 23:22.155
ALL THEY WANT IS
THE FRIED CHICKEN.

23:22.155 --> 23:24.525
THEY'RE NOT USED
TO ANYTHING ELSE, YOU KNOW?

23:24.525 --> 23:26.059
THEY'RE JUST ‐‐
IN THEIR HOOD,

23:26.059 --> 23:28.729
ALL THERE IS
IS A FRIED CHICKEN CHAIN,

23:28.729 --> 23:30.831
THE CHECK CASHIERS,

23:30.831 --> 23:33.266
THE DOLLAR STORE,
AND THE LIQUOR STORE.

23:33.266 --> 23:37.270
THAT'S ALL THERE IS,
SO YOU CAN'T BLAME HER.

23:37.270 --> 23:38.905
WE CAN CLASSIFY ‐‐

23:38.905 --> 23:40.607
[ SIGHS ]

23:42.943 --> 23:45.579
WHY ARE YOU SO ANTSY?

23:45.579 --> 23:48.849
[ SIGHS ]

23:48.849 --> 23:51.051
SIT DOWN!

23:51.051 --> 23:53.620
‐LET'S GO NOW.
‐SIT DOWN.

23:53.620 --> 23:55.822
I SAID SIT DOWN.

24:00.466 --> 24:03.469
♪♪♪♪

24:03.469 --> 24:05.672
GOD, I HATE IT.

24:26.593 --> 24:28.028
THE BOY IS DEAD.

24:28.028 --> 24:29.262
STOP SAYING THAT.

24:29.262 --> 24:30.997
WELL, HE IS.

24:30.997 --> 24:32.999
[ SNIFFLES ]

24:32.999 --> 24:37.671
THERE THEY ARE ‐‐ TEARS.

24:37.671 --> 24:41.508
NOW WHEN YOU STOP DOING
THAT PANSY‐ASS THING

24:41.508 --> 24:43.443
YOU'RE DOING RIGHT NOW,

24:43.443 --> 24:47.514
WE CAN GO VIEW
YOUR PRECIOUS WYATT'S BODY.

24:49.783 --> 24:55.055
BUT YOU GOT TO STOP ALL
THAT SNOTTING AND CRYING.

24:55.055 --> 24:57.323
DO YOU HEAR ME?

24:57.323 --> 24:59.059
AND YOU LISTEN TO ME.

24:59.059 --> 25:03.136
WHEN WE GET OVER TO THE CRYER'S,
YOU WON'T DO THAT.

25:03.136 --> 25:06.573
YOU WILL STAND UP STRAIGHT
LIKE A MAN.

25:06.573 --> 25:10.410
YOU WON'T GO IN THERE
WHIMPERING AND SAPPY.

25:13.079 --> 25:15.015
DO YOU HEAR ME, BOY?

25:17.383 --> 25:21.254
I'M SO GLAD
WE'RE HAVING A BOY.

25:24.224 --> 25:27.260
I CAN GET A DO‐OVER.

25:30.997 --> 25:33.366
I CAN RAISE A MAN...

25:37.671 --> 25:40.473
...NOT LIKE YOU.

25:40.473 --> 25:43.744
EVERY TIME I SEE YOU
WALKING AROUND WITH THEM

25:43.744 --> 25:47.113
TIGHT PANTS
AND FLORAL JACKETS,

25:47.113 --> 25:48.882
ACTING LIKE
SOME KIND OF GIRL ‐‐

25:48.882 --> 25:51.351
JUST JUMPING AND RUNNING
AFTER SOME MAN

25:51.351 --> 25:53.253
LIKE YOU CRAZY,
I CAN'T STAND IT.

25:53.253 --> 25:56.957
I JUST WANT TO CALL QUINCY
TO COME BEAT YOUR ASS AGAIN.

25:59.793 --> 26:02.402
HOW WAS
THAT ASS WHIPPING, HUH?

26:05.205 --> 26:09.643
YOU ‐‐
YOU GOT HIM BACK.

26:09.643 --> 26:13.313
YOU GOT HIM GOOD.

26:13.313 --> 26:15.716
GIRL, YOU DID IT.

26:15.716 --> 26:18.151
YOU DID IT, GIRLFRIEND.

26:20.621 --> 26:24.357
THAT'S IT.

26:24.357 --> 26:28.662
NOW JUST DRY YOUR EYES,
AND WE CAN GO.

26:28.662 --> 26:31.197
I SAID
DRY YOUR EYES, BOY.

26:35.368 --> 26:38.438
THAT'S IT.

26:38.438 --> 26:40.941
THAT'S IT.

26:42.509 --> 26:45.679
ALICE!

26:45.679 --> 26:48.014
THIS BITCH
IS HARD OF HEARING.

26:48.014 --> 26:49.883
ALICE!

26:49.883 --> 26:51.718
YES.

26:51.718 --> 26:52.853
[ SCOFFS ]

26:52.853 --> 26:55.889
UM...I'M SO SORRY, DARLING.

26:55.889 --> 26:57.658
WE ARE GONNA HAVE TO PUT
ALL THE FOOD AWAY.

26:57.658 --> 27:01.067
I'M GONNA HAVE TO GO OUT
AND DEAL WITH SOME FOOLISHNESS.

27:01.067 --> 27:03.604
AND, ALICE...
‐YES.

27:03.604 --> 27:07.140
EVERY SINGLE PIECE OF CLOTHING
THAT MY SON HAS BROUGHT

27:07.140 --> 27:10.544
INTO THIS HOUSE,
THROW IT AWAY, GIVE IT AWAY.

27:10.544 --> 27:13.714
DO ANYTHING WITH IT.
GET IT OUT OF HERE.

27:13.714 --> 27:16.950
I BOUGHT
ALL NEW THINGS FOR YOU.

27:16.950 --> 27:21.387
THEY'RE UPSTAIRS WHEN
YOU GET BACK, OKAY?

27:21.387 --> 27:23.256
THANK YOU.

27:23.256 --> 27:24.758
YES, MA'AM.

27:24.758 --> 27:26.560
MELISSA!

27:30.496 --> 27:32.332
YES.

27:32.332 --> 27:34.835
WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO GO OUT, DEAR.

27:34.835 --> 27:37.571
SO WE'LL CONTINUE THIS
WHEN WE GET BACK, OKAY?

27:37.571 --> 27:39.105
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

27:39.105 --> 27:41.542
YES, JUST ONE OF JEFFERY'S
JUNKIE FRIENDS.

27:41.542 --> 27:43.577
IT'S NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.

27:43.577 --> 27:44.611
IS HE OKAY?

27:44.611 --> 27:46.947
HE'S DEAD, BUT IT'S FINE.

27:46.947 --> 27:48.448
HMM.

27:48.448 --> 27:52.452
SO, ALICE IS GONNA
HELP YOU UNPACK, OKAY?

27:52.452 --> 27:53.486
OKAY.

27:53.486 --> 27:55.121
NOW THERE IS
SOME BUBBLE BATH UPSTAIRS

27:55.121 --> 27:56.156
THAT YOU SHOULD TRY.

27:56.156 --> 27:57.891
IT'S LAVENDER.
IT'S WONDERFUL.

27:57.891 --> 27:59.492
YOU'LL LOVE IT.

27:59.492 --> 28:00.861
I KNOW IT'S SOMETHING JEFFERY'S

28:00.861 --> 28:03.103
GONNA WANT TO GET INTO
WHEN HE GETS BACK.

28:04.538 --> 28:06.873
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

28:06.873 --> 28:08.575
COME ON.

28:13.146 --> 28:15.015
COME ON, BOY.

28:24.090 --> 28:26.292
WHERE YOU GOING?

28:26.292 --> 28:28.461
KISS THIS GIRL.

28:35.902 --> 28:38.038
DO IT AGAIN.

28:38.038 --> 28:41.675
SEE, THAT'S WHAT
FEMININE LIPS TASTE LIKE.

28:41.675 --> 28:43.209
YOU LIKE IT?

28:43.209 --> 28:45.011
TRY IT AGAIN.

28:45.011 --> 28:46.346
DO IT AGAIN.

28:52.753 --> 28:54.688
WE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

28:54.688 --> 28:56.623
WE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

28:56.623 --> 28:58.659
OKAY.
OKAY, SWEETIE, BYE.

28:58.659 --> 29:02.235
BYE.

29:02.235 --> 29:04.404
COME ON,
WE GONNA BE GOOD

29:04.404 --> 29:07.373
COME ON, YOU GONNA DRIVE
YOUR MOMMY?

29:07.373 --> 29:12.546
DRIVE YOUR MOTHER TO THE CRYER'S
TO SEE DEAD WYATT.

29:12.546 --> 29:13.980
COME ON.

29:18.652 --> 29:21.655
♪♪♪♪

29:22.956 --> 29:24.991
[ SIREN WAILING ]

29:34.535 --> 29:37.771
MAN, WHAT DO
THESE FOOLS WANT?

29:37.771 --> 29:39.906
STEP OUT OF THE CAR,
SIR.

29:39.906 --> 29:41.341
MAN,
I AIN'T BREAKING NO LAWS.

29:41.341 --> 29:43.744
STEP OUT OF THE CAR NOW,
SIR.

29:43.744 --> 29:47.380
DAMN.

29:47.380 --> 29:49.516
WALK BACKWARDS WITH YOUR HANDS
ON YOUR HEAD.

29:49.516 --> 29:52.519
‐MAN, I AIN'T DO NOTHING.
‐DO IT NOW, SIR!

29:52.519 --> 29:55.055
MAN, THAT'S SOME BULL
RIGHT HERE, MAN.

29:55.055 --> 29:57.190
‐ON YOUR KNEES, SIR.
‐MAN, LOOK...

29:57.190 --> 29:58.391
ON YOUR KNEES.

29:58.391 --> 29:59.926
DO IT.

29:59.926 --> 30:01.902
ARE YOU
HARD OF HEARING, SIR?

30:08.441 --> 30:10.476
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

30:15.516 --> 30:16.550
MAN, WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

30:16.550 --> 30:17.818
YOU AIN'T GOT TO BE
SO ROUGH, MAN.

30:17.818 --> 30:19.085
I AIN'T EVEN DO NOTHING.

30:19.085 --> 30:20.787
‐YOU GOT YOUR LICENSE ON YOU?
‐IN MY POCKET.

30:20.787 --> 30:22.455
WHAT ABOUT YOUR REGISTRATION
AND INSURANCE?

30:22.455 --> 30:24.958
MAN, YOU NEED TO BE TELLING ME
WHY YOU PULLING ME OVER?

30:24.958 --> 30:27.561
‐CAN WE SEARCH YOUR CAR?
‐NO, YOU CANNOT.

30:27.561 --> 30:29.696
Y'ALL AIN'T GOT PROBABLE CAUSE,
SO I'M NOT GIVING IT TO YOU.

30:29.696 --> 30:32.198
Y'ALL AIN'T GOT NOTHING
ON ME, MAN.

30:32.198 --> 30:34.134
HEY, MAN, YOU AIN'T SUPPOSED
TO BE IN THERE.

30:34.134 --> 30:36.302
WE GOT A CALL ABOUT YOU
DEALING WARLOCK.

30:36.302 --> 30:38.004
MAN,
